Text:
This was the last version developed for OS X.  Unfortunately, that was in 2001.  Considering that - at it's height - Corel Graphics Suite wasn't on par with Adobe, I don't really see ANY appeal in getting this.

I suppose, if you had a file from a design client in a Corel format, this could be useful.  However, I'd be more inclined to convince the client that it should be rebuilt in one of Adobe's fine programs.
